g.text: - name of project to generate code into
- target folder within that project (e.g. src-gen)
- Prefix: namespace prefix of generated code (similar to prefix option in genmodel)
Indicate programming language. The idea is that the GeneratorHint::language attribute is not an arbitrary string (which would be error
prone), but can be selected from a list of available programming languages (i.e. a library with supported languages is required).
A hint how to generate code for elements with upper != 1. fixed: lower=upper, variable: lower=0,
upper=-1, bounded: lower<upper. [typeName] in String will be replaced by type name.
Customize how to trace an element. For complex
types such as lists or pointers

rect.title: A model captures a view of a physical system. It is an abstraction of the physical system, with a certain purpose. This purpose determines what is to be included in the model and what is irrelevant. Thus the model completely describes those aspects of the physical system that are relevant to the purpose of the model, at the appropriate level of detail.

An Element is a constituent of a model. As such, it has the capability of owning other Elements.

A Class classifies a set of objects and specifies the features that characterize the structure and behavior of those objects. A Class may have an internal structure and Ports.

A package can have one or more profile applications to indicate which profiles have been applied. Because a profile is a package, it is possible to apply a profile not only to packages, but also to profiles. Package specializes TemplateableElement and PackageableElement specializes ParameterableElement to specify that a package can be used as a template and a PackageableElement as a template parameter. A package is used to group elements, and provides a namespace for the grouped elements.
